==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Copiousness
<hw>Co"pi*ous*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state or quality of
being copious; abundance; plenty; also, diffuseness in style.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To imitatethe <qex>copiousness</qex> of Homer.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Abudance; plenty; richness; exuberance.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Copist</ent>⟦br⟧
